Jill and the speaker offer their condolences to the families of those killed in a helicopter crash in Ukraine, including Minister of Internal Affairs Denys Monastyrskyy and other Ukrainian government officials. They also express sympathy for the civilians, including children, who were killed or injured. Monastyrskyy and his team were involved in preserving Ukraine's democracy and defending against Russian aggression. The speaker pledges to continue supporting Ukraine's institutions and partnership. They pray for healing and comfort for the wounded and those who lost loved ones. The United States stands with Ukraine in this tragedy for as long as necessary.